    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Linosyris diffusa are infusion, tincture, tea, salve, and decoction. Infusion is made by steeping the leaves and flowers in hot water to treat fever, rheumatism, and respiratory issues. Tincture is extracted using ethanol or glycerol to preserve the plant's volatile oils and is used topically to treat skin conditions and wounds. Tea is prepared by steeping the plant material in hot water and is used to treat fever, coughs, and digestive issues. Decoction is made by boiling the plant material in water to treat conditions such as arthritis and inflammation.",
